---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/UI/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/UI/Footer.astro';

const title = "Adult ADHD assessment";
const description = "A valid clinical assessment is the first step in managing ADHD. Use of DIVA-5, differential diagnosis and design of an individualized treatment plan.";
const canonicalURL = "https://drgkikas.com/en/ypiresies/adhd-evaluation";

const schemaBundle = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "MedicalProcedure",
      "name": title,
      "description": description,
      "url": canonicalURL
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://drgkikas.com/en" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://drgkikas.com/en/ypiresies" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": title, "item": canonicalURL }
      ]
    }
  ]
});
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} schema={schemaBundle}>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-slate-50 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <!-- Breadcrumbs UI -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-8 mt-4">
        <ol class="list-none p-0 inline-flex flex-wrap items-center">
          <li class="flex items-center"><a href="/en" class="hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors">Home</a><svg class="w-3 h-3 mx-2 opacity-50" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></li>
          <li class="flex items-center"><a href="/en/ypiresies/" class="hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors">Services</a><svg class="w-3 h-3 mx-2 opacity-50" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></li>
          <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-slate-800 font-medium">{title}</span></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <div class="glass-card p-10 md:p-16">
        <div class="text-center mb-16 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-8 leading-normal">{title}</h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">{description}</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg md:prose-xl prose-blue max-w-none text-slate-700
          prose-p:mb-10 prose-p:leading-[1.9]
          prose-headings:text-blue-900 prose-headings:font-bold 
          prose-h2:mt-20 prose-h2:mb-8 prose-h2:border-b prose-h2:border-slate-100 prose-h2:pb-4
          prose-h3:mt-14 prose-h3:mb-6
          prose-a:font-bold prose-a:text-blue-900 prose-a:bg-blue-100 prose-a:px-2 prose-a:py-0.5 prose-a:rounded-lg prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:bg-blue-700 hover:prose-a:text-white prose-a:transition-colors
          prose-ul:my-10 prose-li:my-5 marker:text-blue-500">
          
          <h2>The clinical assessment process</h2>
          <p>Assessment of ADHD in adults is a complex clinical process that goes beyond completing a simple questionnaire. At Smart CNS Center, we follow international standards to ensure diagnostic accuracy, focusing both on the presence of symptoms and, most importantly, on the functional impairment they cause.</p>
          <p>The goal is not simply to apply a diagnostic label, but to map the way your brain processes information, time and emotions.</p>

          <h2>What the assessment includes</h2>
          <p>The process is usually completed in 1 to 2 sessions and includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Detailed developmental history</strong>: ADHD is neurodevelopmental, therefore symptoms must have been present before the age of 12. We explore your trajectory from school years to adult life.</li>
            <li><strong>DIVA-5 semi-structured interview</strong>: A modern, validated tool — Diagnostic Interview for ADHD in Adults — which examines DSM-5 criteria through specific examples from everyday life.</li>
            <li><strong>Differential diagnosis</strong>: It is essential to exclude or identify conditions such as:
              <ul>
                <li>Anxiety disorders and depression</li>
                <li>Sleep disorders, such as sleep apnea</li>
                <li>Burnout or chronic stress</li>
                <li>Personality disorders</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Why an online test is not enough</h2>
          <p>Online “tests” can only provide an indication. Clinical assessment is necessary because:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Masking</strong>: Many adults have developed skills that hide ADHD, making simple questionnaires inaccurate.</li>
            <li><strong>Overlap</strong>: Symptoms such as inattention or impulsivity may be caused by other psychiatric or medical conditions.</li>
            <li><strong>Treatment plan</strong>: A diagnosis without a management plan has limited clinical value.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>After diagnosis: the next step</h2>
          <p>After the assessment, you receive detailed feedback and we design your treatment plan together. This may include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Psychoeducation</li>
            <li>Organizational strategies</li>
            <li>Pharmacotherapy, when clinically indicated, with continuous medical follow-up</li>
            <li>Precision psychiatry, including possible PGx assessment for safer medication selection</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="mt-20 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-8">FAQ</h2>
            <div class="space-y-8">
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Do I need to bring old school records?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">If school reports or previous assessments are available, they are very useful. However, the assessment can still be completed without them through retrospective clinical history-taking.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">What if my symptoms are caused by anxiety?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">That is precisely the role of differential diagnosis. If anxiety is the primary cause, treatment is adapted accordingly. If anxiety is secondary to ADHD, treating ADHD may also improve anxiety symptoms.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Is an official certificate issued?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">Yes. A medical report can be provided for any lawful use, such as work or studies.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Internal Links for SEO -->
        <div class="mt-20 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-8">Related Conditions & Diagnoses</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a href="/en/diataraxes/adhd-adult/" class="p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100 hover:border-blue-300 transition-all font-bold text-blue-900">Adult ADHD &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/en/diataraxes/agxodeis-diataraxes/" class="p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100 hover:border-blue-300 transition-all font-bold text-blue-900">Anxiety Disorders &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
